{"questionId":"9074085","questionHtml":"<p>An object moves in a circle of constant radius. Values of the centripetal force <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>F</mi></math> are measured&nbsp;for different values of angular velocity <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ω</mi></math>. A graph is plotted with <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ω</mi></math> on the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-axis. Which quantity&nbsp;plotted on the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math>-axis will produce a straight-line graph?</p>\n<p>A.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mi>F</mi></msqrt></math></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>F</mi></math></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>F</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>F</mi></mfrac></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>A</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9074085","referenceCode":"21M.1.SL.TZ2.23","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"An object moves in a circle of constant radius. Values of the centripetal force F are measured for different values of angular velocity ω. A graph is plotted with ω on the x-axis. ","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"23","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 6: Circular motion and gravitation","6.1 – Circular motion","Core","Topic 6: Circular motion and gravitation"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}